parameters: Rei: ...
Luno: Rei, I knew you'd be here.
Rei: Luno, thank you.
Luno: How's the magic practice going?

Rei: Not well. Maybe they're right, maybe I'm just not cut out for
this.
Luno: I see.

Rei: At this point, being able to cast Fire is like a middle schooler
finally learning multiplication. All this practice does is get me
down.
Rei: Honestly, I'm starting to hate it.
Luno: I see...

Luno: Hey Rei, do you really have to become a sorceress no matter
what?
Rei: Eh...

Luno: You don't have to be so stubborn about it. There are plenty of
sorcerers in the world. Isn't there something only you can do?
Rei: Something only I can do?
Luno: Why not become an idol?

Luno: Earlier, a representative from an entertainment company that
develops idols came to your house. They left this business card and
documents for you to give to Rei.

Luno: You're so cute, Rei, that people just can't leave you alone. How
many times have you received idol offers now? If you became an idol, I
could brag about it too.

Luno: This is the contract that could make you an idol. I've made sure
to hand it over.
$kami
$kami
Rei: ...

Luno: Ahh! Why would you tear it up?! That was your chance to become
an idol!!
Luno: Why would you do such a thing?!
Rei: I'm not an idol. I have no interest in that.
Rei: Luno, do you want to become an idol manager or something?
Luno: Rei, I'm sorry... I didn't consider your feelings.
Rei: As long as you understand.

Luno: Yeah... But you know, being an idol is a respectable dream job
too. There are so many girls who want to become idols but can't. It's
honestly a waste because you have more than enough potential.

Rei: That's something others have decided for me. I never once said I
wanted to be an idol.
Rei: I am a sorceress.
Rei: Sorceress Rei Granford.

Rei: Right now, I might be a failure as a sorceress. But one day, I'll
show those guys and make them eat their words.
Luno: Alright, I get it. You win, Rei. You've got me beat.
Luno: But what about your progress with magic?
Rei: ...

Rei: A year ago, I applied for baptism in the magical kingdom of
Valentina. I haven't heard back yet though.

Luno: Baptism in the magical kingdom of Valentina? The ceremony where
low-ranking sorcerers from around the world receive magical power from
the Queen of Valentina? But I heard the competition is so fierce that
it's impossible to get selected.

Rei: Yes, but... I don't think I'll make any more progress with magic
practice. I've done everything I could, but it's no use. My only
option left is to go to Valentina for the baptism.

Luno: But... that's impossible. Only one person is chosen out of tens
of thousands in this country alone. How many sorcerers do you think
there are in the world? It's a fairy tale.
Rei: But that's all I have to bet on.
Rei: It's getting late. Let's head back home.
Mary: Rei~!!! It's terrible~!!!
Rei: ???
Mary: Rei! It's terrible!
Rei: Mom, what's wrong?
Ron: It's terrible! Terrible! Terrible!
Rei: Dad too... What's wrong with both of you?
Mary: Va, Valentina sent a letter! Rei! You can receive the baptism!
Rei: Eh...
Rei: Eh---!!!? Really!!!?

Mary: There's no mistake! It has the signature of the Queen of
Valentina.

Luno: Rei has been selected for the baptism in Valentina...
Unbelievable... A fairy tale has become reality...
Mary: Rei, I'm so happy for you. Your dream has come true.

Rei: No way... I can't believe such a miracle is really happening. It
feels like I'm still dreaming.
Luno: Rei, I'm glad your dream came true.
Rei: Yeah...

Luno: But I wonder why Rei was chosen. Considering the competition
rate...

Ron: Hmm, Rei gets offers to be an idol so often because she's
especially cute. There must have been male judges who took a liking to
her. It has nothing to do with magic.
Luno: I see, that's why she caught their eye.

Rei: By the way, Mom, when do we leave for the magical kingdom of
Valentina?

Mary: Next month. Your father and I are going too. What about you,
Luno-kun?

Luno: Of course, I'm going too! If any guys try to get close to Rei,
I'll knock them out~.
Rei: Ahaha, Luno, can you really do that~?
Luno: Ye, ye, yes I can~!
Rei: Ahaha, Luno, you're so funny.

Mary: Now that it's decided, I'll reply to Valentina's letter. Rei,
you're really lucky to be able to receive the baptism. It's like a
miracle...

Rei: Thank you. Dad, Mom, Luno. I will definitely go to Valentina. And
I will receive the baptism.
Ron: Well, it's about time we got hungry, let's go home.
Rei: Yeah.
Rei: I can go to Valentina. It still feels like I'm dreaming.
Rei: I will do my best in Valentina.
